The allegations, if true, would constitute a grave breach of the nation's organ transplant rules, as well as a public relations setback for those promoting organ donation.
At present there are no specific rules on organ donation to foreigners.
Russian lawmakers adopted on first reading a law which will allow local hospitals to remove and transplant organs, something only the big hospitals have been allowed to do.
